<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-445-531  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 445 531.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Sept 20 1990 n1232 p58(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Think before you pay. (buying a personal computer) (Buying Guide)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lang, Kathy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>One of the key things to consider before buying a computer is theproblem that the computer will solve.andP;  It is then easier tospecify systems to meet their needs.andP;  Consistency in installationis also an important aspect since it is always advantageous tohave the same system across as many users as possible.andP;  Duringperiods of sickness and holidays, for example, such an arrangementenables users to cover for each other.andP;  This also ensures that thesoftware will carry on the same performance, with the samekeystrokes on all systems, and it minimizes maintenance whileincreasing the value of training.andP;  It is also sometimes moreprudent to choose software before hardware, which helps ensurethat they work together.andP;  Of equal importance is the company thatsells your software and hardware.andP;  It is best to deal with acompany that has a good reputation for supporting its end users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Equipment AcquisitionHardware SelectionMicrocomputersGuidelines.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>